                                   ╭────────╮
                                   │Overview│
                                   ╰────────╯
      This directory contains the documentation and bootstrap source code
  for the Nil programming language. The documentation is located in the 'doc/'
           folder. The source code is contained in the 'src/' folder.

                                 ╭────────────╮
                                 │Installation│
                                 ╰────────────╯
      The source code requires only a standards compliant C compiler to be 
    available in the executable path. A Makefile is provided to assist with
                      compilation but it is not required.

Compilation produces a single executable file with no dependencies which may be
            installed and executed anywhere in the operating system.

                                ╭─────────────╮
                                │Documentation│
                                ╰─────────────╯
  The documentation is supplied in HTML format which should be viewable using 
             any web browser. There are several "books" provided...

                        "The Standard Definition of Nil"

                      "Default, Supplement, and Auxiliary"

                          "Learn to Program with Nil"

                           "Nil for the C Programmer"

                        "Formalization and Proof in Nil"